text: The 1933 Spanish general election was an election held on 19 November 1933 during the Second Republic. The right increased its share of votes and won against the governing left-wing coalition. Before these elections the Spanish Constitution of 1931 was approved, which recognized the right of women to vote. These were the first elections in the history of Spain in which women voted. ==Notes== Category:1930s in Spain Category:Spanish general elections Category:1933 in Europe
title: 1933 Spanish general election
